de the Catholic subculture at both the grass-roots and the elite levels. The result is a substantial contribution to our understanding of the interaction of religion and politics in a plural society and the sources of party loyalty and subcultural cohesion.  aMode of access: Internet via World Wide Web.  aIn English.0 aDescription based on online resource; title from PDF title page (publisher's Web site, viewed 29. Mai 2023) 7aRELIGION / Christianity / Catholic.2bisacsh40uhttps://doi.org/10.1515/978077356077240uhttps://www.degruyter.com/isbn/9780773560772423Coveruhttps://www.degruyter.com/document/cover/isbn/9780773560772/original  aGBV-deGruyter-alles